This paper focuses on predicting the impact of academic publications, which is a common topic in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper uses a large dataset from an online academic service, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also examines the influence of the publication venue, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computer and society (cs.CY). Finally, the paper's focus on quantifying scientific impact could potentially fall under the sub-category of scientific computing (cs.SD).
